{
  "texts": [
    "The first key category, or facet of the taxonomy, that emerged is Practitioner Awareness.",
    "This category emerged from two underlying concepts: AI ethics & principles-related awareness and team-related awareness.",
    "The majority of articles reported that the developers participating in their study were aware of ethics, including its importance [G1], [G4], [G5], [G17], and its relevance [G18],[G8] in AI.",
    "Few studies [G1], [G23] reported that 'Transparency' was one of the ethical principles of AI that were discussed widely by the AI practitioners who participated in their studies and a highlighted topic of discussion in academia [G6].",
    "Most AI practitioners who participated in studies [G9], [G18] were aware of the term 'transparent AI' and it was recognised as a goal during AI development."
  ]
}